text.tspan: Workshopper is the name used for the
open source lesson modules associated
with NodeSchool. All are self guided (you
don't need to attend a workshop to do one)
and most work offline.
Workshoppers come in two flavours: Core
and Electives.
Core workshoppers focus on essential skills
for working with Node.js like basic
JavaScript skills, Git and GitHub, npm and
Markdown.
Electives are workshoppers on popular
libraries or styles of writing Node.js. There
are about 40 electives available, and its
number is growing.
You’ll need Node.js on your computer to
get started with each of these. Then use
npm (it comes with Node) to install each
module. Once installed, simply type the
workshopper’s name to launch.
